GitHub.pavan Pk branch

    - GitHub is the Repository.

    - GitHub Repository is the Open Source Repository and Maintained By Google.

    - Git is the Tool used to interact with the GitHub.

GitHub Operations.

1.Create the Repository (Locally)

2.Set the User Credentials to the Local Repository.

3.Create the Files in Local Repository.

4.Commit the Files to the Repository.

5.Creating the Branch

6.Merging the Code

7.Merge Conflicts

8.Working the Cloud Repositories

9.Integration Of GitHub to IDE'S - WebStrom , Ecilipse , Visual Studio.

10.Commit the Code to Cloud Repository

11.Push the Code

12.Pull the Code

13.Code Comparision in IDE'S

            ***************************************
1.Create the Repository (Locally)
-
    Download and Install the Git.
    -
    website : https://git-scm.com/download/win
    file name : Git-2.13.0-64-bit.exe

    Create Folder in any drive.
    -
    E:/githubdemo

    Execute the Following Command by using Git Bash
    -
    >git init

  [ Note . automatically 'githubdemo' converted as local repository ]

                *******************************
2. Add the User Credentials to the Local Repository.

>git config --global user.name "NareshIT"
>git config --global user.email "hr@nareshit.in"

                **********************************

3. Create the Files to the Repository.

>touch demo.js

[Note . automatically "demo.js" file will be created in repository]

                ************************************

4.Commit the Files to the Repository.

>git add demo.js
>git commit
>press "i"
>type "initial commit"
>press "esc"
>type ":wq"
>press "enter"


From 2nd Commit Onwards.
-
>git add demo.js
>git commit -m "Custom Message"


Status Of Git.
-
>git status

log of Git
-
>git log

            *****************************
5.Create the Branch.
-
>git branch developer_one
>git checkout developer_one


            *****************************

6. Merge the Code.

>git merge developer_one








